    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to Mr. Paul A. Rockwell <date value="1916-06-08">June 8th [1916]</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-06-08">June 8th [1916]</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Paul:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            Rain &amp; clouds
            and there has been
            nothing doing.  Only news
            is that Bar le Duc has
            been closed to us for
            some fool reason.  
            Rumsey has arrived and
            will be working in a 
            couple of days.
            </p><p>
            Mr. Prince was out
            as you probaboy know.
            He told us the story 
            of Doc Wheeler and his
            
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            passport.  Seems to
            me you have there
            a good chance to
            lay it into the States
            for fair.
            </p><p>
            There seems to
            be a split up in this
            outfit.  Thaw &amp; Co. V.
            Cowden, Prince et al.  I
            don’t give a damn and
            won’t join either Club.
            </p><p>
            Received a letter from
            Betty written in her own
            hand so I guess she’s
            coming along well.
            
            <pb n="[p.3]"/>
            
            Have my new machine
            now and will be ready
            again to morrow I expect.
            </p><p>
            Have just heard how
            A.A. ^American Ambulance hogged front seats
            at Memorial Service.  Lord
            I’d lay it into them.
            You’ve got the Thaw 
            incident to bolster up
            with as well.  Even the 
            fellows in the field
            sections have no use 
            for the damned crowd.
            Lovell, Barclay and Willis
            are leaving to join
            
            <pb n="[p.4]"/>
            
            Aviation.  Lovell is A I.,
            but others aren’t much.
            Hope Bill is getting on
            well.  I wrote him the
            other day.
            </p><p>
            Did I tell you Marcelle
            wrote me a “I’ll go to you
            if wounded” note.  The 
            net is drawing closer<unclear>[.]</unclear>
            </p><p>
            Excuse rotten letter but
            I’m in a big rush
            getting machine fixed up.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>My best</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim.</signed>
        		</closer>
        		
            
